  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6116",
  "title": "InstantSearch component updating status inside unrelated InstantSearch component ",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nConsider this scenario:\r\n```\r\n<Header>\r\n   <InstantSearch id=\"1\" {...relevantProps}>\r\n       <SearchBox />\r\n   </InstantSearch>\r\n</Header>\r\n\r\n<SearchPage>\r\n   <InstantSearch id=\"2\" {...relevantProps}>\r\n       <SearchBox style={{ display: \"none\" }} />\r\n       <Hits />\r\n   </InstantSearch>\r\n</SearchPage>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe issue is that inside SearchPage I want the loading state of the second (id: 2) instantsearch component. I do this with the useInstantSearch hook to retrieve the status. The peculiar thing is that whenever I click the SearchBox in the header (id: 1), the status of the second InstantSearch component reacts to this and updates the status object, setting it to \"loading\", then \"stalled\", then \"idle\".\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nTry above scenario.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nn/a\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nI expect the status state to be seperate and not react to unrelated InstantSearch components.\n\n### Package version\n\ninstantsearch.js@4.66.1, react-instantsearch@7.7.1\n\n### Operating system\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Browser\n\nChrome 122.0.6261.131\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
